---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '@/components/Navbar';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Typography & Color - Web Interfaces">
  <Navbar client:idle />
  
  <main class="lg:ml-64 min-h-screen bg-white">
    <!-- Header -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-16 pt-20 lg:pt-16 pb-12 lg:pb-16 border-b border-gray-200">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center text-gray-600 hover:text-black transition-colors mb-6">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
          </svg>
          Back
        </a>
        <h1 class="main-text gradient-text mb-4">
          Typography & Color
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg lg:text-xl text-gray-600">
          Exploring the principles of typography and color theory in web design.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Introduction -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-16 py-12 lg:py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-semibold text-black mb-6">Design Principles</h2>
        <p class="text-base lg:text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Typography and color are foundational elements of web design. They work together to create hierarchy, 
          establish mood, and guide users through digital experiences. Understanding these principles is essential 
          for creating effective and beautiful interfaces.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base lg:text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          This section explores best practices for choosing typefaces, creating type scales, establishing color palettes, 
          and ensuring accessibility in your designs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Divider -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-16">
      <div class="border-t border-gray-200"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Core Concepts -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-16 py-12 lg:py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-semibold text-black mb-8">Core Concepts</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-10">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">1. Typographic Hierarchy</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Create clear visual hierarchy through size, weight, and spacing. Use type scales to maintain consistency 
              and ensure readability across different screen sizes and contexts.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">2. Color Psychology</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Colors evoke emotions and associations. Understanding color psychology helps you choose palettes that 
              support your brand message and create the right emotional response in users.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">3. Contrast & Accessibility</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Ensure sufficient contrast between text and backgrounds to maintain readability. Follow WCAG guidelines 
              to make your designs accessible to users with visual impairments.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">4. Responsive Typography</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Typography should adapt gracefully across devices. Use fluid type scales and responsive units to ensure 
              text remains readable and proportional on all screen sizes.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">5. Color Systems</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Build systematic color palettes with primary, secondary, and semantic colors. Create clear naming conventions 
              and document usage guidelines to maintain consistency across your design system.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">6. Performance Considerations</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Optimize font loading strategies and choose web-safe fonts when possible. Balance aesthetic choices with 
              performance to ensure fast page loads and smooth rendering.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Divider -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-16">
      <div class="border-t border-gray-200"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Best Practices -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-16 py-12 lg:py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-semibold text-black mb-8">Best Practices</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black mb-2">Limit Font Families</h4>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Use 2-3 font families maximum. Too many typefaces create visual noise and slow down page load times.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black mb-2">Establish Line Length</h4>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Maintain optimal line length of 45-75 characters for readability. Use max-width constraints on text containers.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black mb-2">Test Color Combinations</h4>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Always test color combinations for accessibility. Use tools to verify contrast ratios meet WCAG standards.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black mb-2">Use Color Purposefully</h4>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Don't rely solely on color to convey information. Combine color with icons, text, or patterns for clarity.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Main text - responsive sizing */
  .main-text {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 28px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .main-text {
      font-size: 42px;
      line-height: 44px;
    }
  }

  /* Gradient text - more subtle */
  .gradient-text {
    background: linear-gradient(to right, #6b7280, #374151, #1f2937);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }
</style>

